snippet.textDisplay: This is totally beyond my comprehension why Coke Studio is ruining the feel of music with these out-of-context music videos. Madari was such a great track with a sense of mysticism through lyrics and energy through music. This video totally ruined it. The Tandava-style dance was great but the story of "Faith is Happiness" that you were trying to tell with it just does not fit with the soul of the song that Madari was (is). I am not against music videos; I won't say that you must stick to studio sessions only but the videos have to do justice to the wonderful music that we are creating. Hope someone at Coke Studio is noting our concerns.
